// A one-shot request/acknowledge handshake, in the Stratum surface syntax.
//
// `new` mints two distinct fresh channel names from nil (assigned in
// declaration order): req = @0, ack = @(@0!(0)). It is name-generation, not
// restriction — see `stratum expand` for the raw quoted-process term.
//
// The client sends a request on `req`; the server receives it (binding the
// reply value `x`, unused here) and answers by emitting on `ack`.

new req, ack

req!(0) | req(x).ack!(0)
